reviews.review_text: There was not a huge selection of fish when I visited. The fish they did have looked very healthy and well looked after. Ill definitely be going back.
Really good place to go for shrimp. I got some really impressive blue caridina shrimp. They also have n impressive selection of high quality gold fish an koi. Aquariums are well run.
Prices are a little higher than Amazon or Petsmart but the owner is super knowledgable and friendly.

The store interior could use some more light, but has everything you need. Lots of selection, and beautiful koi as well. I dont understand the bad reviews, I asked questions and was helped quickly and nicely.
Lots of variety  of fish from big to small Specialize in fancy goldfish and koi All fish on own filter and always in quarantine. No shared water .

I dont know why this place has bad reviews?? Well hopefully this great review will steer others to this place. It was our first time here yesterday.  We came in just before closing (a habit of ours. Lol) and SAM was  very helpful and patient with us. Even though we arrived quite late he didnt rush us at all and we were able to take our time in selecting our first koi fish. Sam has a wide selection of koi fish....much more then ANY of the other places weve first over the last week. The customer service we received was awesome. Sam was very accommodating with our first purchase here. We will definitely be returning. As a matter of fact well be going back today!! We will travel the distance (we live in Burnaby/Coquitlam area), for the quality of service we received. Also, from what I understand this is a long time, family run business and its better to support the local community then the bigger chain stores like Pet Smart, Bosley etc.
They have big experience with fish, although their prices are not bad. I can tell you, they are run by asians who can tell you all sorts of ways to keep your fish healthy.

Helpful service. Reasonable prices. Good staff. Quick purchase was easy. Good social distancing. Helpful for me being new to buying fish tanks and rocks. All fish were happy in store and it was super clean including the tanks. :)

I was looking for a 20 year old part for a filter. No one in Canada had them but I called these guys and they looked around and found one for me. They definitely are not going to hold a long conversation with you but my experience was really good. PS I only looked at the discus and they were looking good, clean tank, etc. Maybe not the best for customer service but they do seem to know what theyre doing.

I had some troubles keeping my fish alive and was at a loss for why. The last pet store I had gone to had just told me they had short life spans. I went to this one because it was closer to where I am currently living, and asked them what I had done wrong. They had gotten to my problem pretty quickly and the solution made a lot of sense. I see no problems with the store. The service was great, and the fish are very vibrant and healthy. I think this place deserves a better rating than what it gets now. I will be coming back for more fish from now on.

Excellent store been going there for years.  I am 73 years old and I think the boys do a great job. It is a shame that kids now a days have to put down businesses.  Back in my day this was not the case.  I recommend Main Aquarium to any fish hobby person.
Love this store! Our go to store for unique and healthy fish, especially goldfish and koi
Not a big shop but they surprisingly have quite a bit of selection of fish and aquarium supplies. Great spot, easy to get parking and its right in my neighbourhood. Love it.
Awesome local aquarium store with a great selection and quality fish.
Good prices on fish! The prices are really reasonable here. You can find fish that you can t find at pet smart. The owner is knowledgeable about all the fish in the store.
It has a variety of fish at reasonable pricing. Plenty of options for the decor too. Love this place. I would definitely go back and suggest this place to public.
Great selection of fish, Ive seen several species here you cant get many other places in the lower mainland. Ive bought several discus fish here and theyre absolutely gorgeous!
If you looking for koi the selection is amazing. Great tank maintenance. Awesome staff. And fish necessities on point.
Excellent quick service with a nice welcoming atmosphere. The fish here are very nice, vibrant, and are treated very well. The nasty comments below are very misleading and are extremely exaggerated.
Place seemed cleaner after my visit from 6 months ago. Lots of fish supplies and I definetly reccomend this place!
Excellent selection of exotic and rare fish. Prices are very competitive and provide very good service.

The employeesame are helpfull I been with them about 2 years buyin fish and fish food from them. Just awsome but I miss the fraser 22nd its bigger but on main and 48th close for me to get the fish food supply.
Visited the store recently to buy my niece some fish.  Great staff/customer service and my niece is sooo happy with her gift! :)
Been with these guys since they were on Fraser. Always worth a look when in the neighborhood, never know what they might have in stock.
Really clean and organized
The fish are very healthy and inexpensive!  There are a lot more types of fish than other pet stores.
I always make a point of going here for my fish and supplies. Nice store and lots of options.
Very nice guy that works there always willing to work with ya and order stuff if he doesnt carry it
Good advice about buying water pump. Gave me extra free filter materials as well.
Good dry goods.

Big selection of supplies and have bought many fish there. I visit monthly
Great selection.   Street parking and small area in back.
Reasonable prices, great selection. I miss this place.

Great staff, good selection and prices.

Pleasant and I just liked the place.

Dark and dimly lit this Aquarium is a great stop to walk around a visit the excitable fish in the tanks. My friends got a fish here and think fondly of it. Overall very chill atmosphere and you can spend a long tike just looking at them, so honestly its a good time.
Good quality and healthy fish. Lots of selection.

Average store..limited unique varieties You definitely can find your fish supplies for home aquarium.. Great customer service..they treat loyal customers very well..but needs a little bit improvement It is my favorite store Fish tanks are taken care of..fish health is great. I build a fluval panoramic aquarium...looks great.. Thanks Sam!

A great stock in aquarium supplies and high quality fish. My main interest is discus and I find that the quality of these types of fish are to a higher standard that some other stores Ive been to. Very apparent that Sam knows his stuff as he is very knowledgeable and can take the time to explain if you are uncertain about certain areas of the hobby.

When I had walked into the store, the first thing that tranced into my mind first, was the glimpse of the neatness of the product ailses. Everything  in the compartment of wares were decently organized, so you could really scroll through the store with ease. The pricing was reasonable, sometimes the products were cheaper by a couple of bucks and some other products that were very expensive, for instance, seachem paraguard-250 ml being priced at a whoping $30. The fish tanks had a excessively a average price on them, so nothing special about that, although some of the tanks were more on the expensive side. So pricing was pretty standard for an average store like this. There was a lot of selection on meds, fish foods filter medias at a pretty cheap price, so this was one of the few things that stood out from this store. Now, the fish selection. The pricing was fairly reasonable and there exceedingly lots of fish to choose from. Some of the fish were very appealing, their colors gleaming across the glass, for instance, the cardinal tetras and rummy nose tetras. They were a standout for me, because the quality and the looks of the cardinal tetras were some of the most colourful ones I had ever seen in my 15 years of pain, compared to aquariums west, which looked like the terrified faces of the people dying at Travis Scotts Astroworld concert. Most of the fish were healthy, however I had spotted a couple of dead or dying fish in the tanks, and several of the tanks were very cloudy and filthy, for instance, the goldfish tank, so that is one thing to improve on in this store, is to have a daily check on the fish, and quarantine sick fish and dispose dead fish. One thing I was dissapointed in, was the bettas in cups. They were unfiltered, and was very cramped, so next time try to make a filtered betta set up and try to upgrade the cups to small acrylic tanks. Finally, the customer service needs a bit of improvement, because the owner looks like he experienced vietnam flashbacks. When I did some communication with him, he didnt show much enthusiasm and  replied to me in a monotonous manner. Also when I was try to pick a schooling fish for my 32.5 gallon aquarium, he did what the call the asian death stare(my dad does this a lot) so it was a bit uncomfortable, felt like I was the victim of the John F Kennedy assasination, but eventually I got a bit used to it. Henceforth, this is a pretty good, average fish store with a couple of quirks, and I reccomend this store to anyone who doesnt care too much about customer service, but wants some high quality schooling or centerpiece fish including a good selection of fish supplies.

Great little shop jam packed with future pet fish.  Lots of koi especially of all types and sizes all the way to a foot long! The fish look all in good health and well kept otherwise. We keep coming by to have a look at all the different varieties and imagining ourselves having a giant tank with them all. The prices seem reasonable, although the arowanda is pricey; so beautiful though! There is much selection of both freshwater and saltwater supplies as well. The only thing preventing 5 stars is that the owner/operators are always a bit surly as they seem to resent the looking and want you to buy something; but they are not verbal about it. regardless, its like a real aquarium in the neighborhood and me and kids love it.

I bought my 75 gallons tank from this store way back from their previous location at Fraser street. The old guy seems off and not so accomodating but the young guy is way so helpful. But I like the way it is though because you can roam around without someone bothering you till you are ready to buy and ask questions and then they will help you out.
Lots of interesting fish there for sale.

Good aquarium shop! The staff/owners are not the most social but will accommodate if you speak up and ask the right questions. Good selection of tropical fish and conveniently located. Its getting much tougher these days to find a well stocked aquarium shop in a central location.....

For all the reviews saying the water is dirty, it is not, in fact it is just tannin in the water done purposefully. They have a good selection of stuff.  For example, I needed almond leaves, cholla wood and some Hikari food for my shrimp and shrimp tank, and their prices are fairly reasonable.  I do agree the owner isnt the most personable but if you ask he will give knowledgable answers. At the end of the day I got what I needed.
Nice selection on fishes, owner was helpful when I had questions. A little bit on pricier side, which was 20percent less from a different store with the same quality.

This is where I go for quality food for my pond fish. And I can get anything there, pumps included. Great bunch of guys. Just double check their address because I think that they are now on Fraser, not Main.
